summary: Okay so here’s the truth...As much as I disagree with Sansa questioning Jons decisions it’s realistic. Like you will not find...
body: Okay so here’s the truth…As much as I disagree with Sansa questioning Jons decisions it’s realistic. Like you will not find two siblings or a ruler and thier advisor/consulatant/sisterthing who always agree. There will always be things that they will argue on!! Let’s be real Sansa might betray Jon but not in the “turn the north against him and make myself the queen” way but more in the “I’m gonna make some decisions that don’t include making alliances with Daenerys”. In my opinion Jon did the right thing by bending the knee to Daenerys cause they need all the help they can get for the white walkers and she has dragons so I’m pretty sure the north AND SANSA will be cool with it eventually. Sansa is still a pain tho tbh but I’m praying D&D will actually write her as the cool character that she is.
